        "title": "How to mock declared class in private method using mockito",
        "body": "<p>I am writing junit test to test the private method which has class declared in it.<\/p>\n<p>My code:<\/p>\n<pre><code>private Object getFunctReturn()\n {\n   InterfaceName obj = new ClassName():\n   Map map = obj.getMap();\n   map.foreach()-&gt;{\n            //iterating map here....\n   }\n }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>I am using WhiteBox api to test private methods. How can I mock InterfaceName obj = new ClassName(); so that  i can proceed to for next execution of code?<\/p>\n",
